ZH: 我背着沉重的担子去市场。
EN: I carried a heavy burden on my back to the market.

ZH: 她接过我手中的担子。
EN: She took the burden from my hands.

ZH: 他放下了心里的担子，终于可以松口气了。
EN: He let go of the burden in his heart and finally breathed a sigh of relief.

ZH: 这个困难真是一个不小的担子。
EN: This difficulty is really a big burden.

ZH: 我忍受着屋顶上的担子压力。
EN: I bear the pressure of the burdens on the roof.

ZH: 这副画的担子给我留下了深刻的印象。
EN: The burden in this painting left a deep impression on me.

ZH: 拿担子的女人弯曲着背。
EN: The woman with the burden bent her back.

ZH: 担子的重量让他们艰难前行。
EN: The weight of the burden made it difficult for them to move forward.

ZH: 我拿着沉重的担子，艰难地走上山顶。
EN: I carried a heavy burden and walked up the hill with difficulty.

ZH: 昨天晚上我把担子从车上卸了下来。
EN: Last night, I unloaded the burden from the car.

ZH: 这个担子的破裂得很严重，必须修复。
EN: This burden is severely cracked and needs to be repaired.

ZH: 他手上的担子太重，几乎无法移动。
EN: The burden in his hands was too heavy to move.

ZH: 她的肩膀上挑着担子，一边走一边唱歌。
EN: She carried the burden on her shoulders and sang while walking.

ZH: 请把担子放在这边，我会处理的。
EN: Please put the burden here, I will handle it.

ZH: 这个新员工接管了我手中的担子。
EN: This new employee took over the burden from my hands.

ZH: 担子的形状决定了它的用途。
EN: The shape of the burden determines its purpose.

ZH: 家里的担子全部由我一人来承担。
EN: I alone bear all the burdens at home.

ZH: 她忍累揹起了担子，为了家人的未来。
EN: She endured weariness and carried the burden for the future of her family.

ZH: 这个壮年男子将担子绑在背上，准备离开。
EN: The middle-aged man tied the burden to his back and prepared to leave.

ZH: 父亲教我怎样扛起沉重的担子。
EN: Father taught me how to carry heavy burdens.
